# Cobb County Jail Inquiry Scraper

Apify actor that searches the Cobb County jail roster using **Inquiry mode** with **WebShare rotating proxies**.

## Repo Structure

```
cobb-jail-scraper/
├── .actor/
│   └── actor.json       ← Apify actor config & input schema
├── main.js              ← Main Playwright scraper code
├── package.json         ← Node.js dependencies
└── README.md
```

## How to Deploy on Apify

1. Push this repo to GitHub (keep it **Private**)
2. Go to [apify.com](https://apify.com) → **Actors** → **Create new**
3. Choose **"Link to GitHub"**
4. Select this repo
5. Set main file to `main.js`
6. Click **Build**

## Input Parameters

| Field | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `name` | ✅ | Inmate name in `Last First` format e.g. `Smith John` |
| `mode` | ✅ | `Inquiry` or `In Custody` |
| `proxyUsername` | ✅ | WebShare proxy username |
| `proxyPassword` | ✅ | WebShare proxy password |
| `proxyList` | ✅ | Array of proxy IPs e.g. `["12.34.56.78:8080"]` |
| `soid` | ❌ | SOID number (faster lookup) |
| `serial` | ❌ | Serial number |

## Example Input

```json
{
  "name": "Smith John",
  "mode": "Inquiry",
  "proxyUsername": "your_webshare_username",
  "proxyPassword": "your_webshare_password",
  "proxyList": [
    "12.34.56.78:8080",
    "23.45.67.89:8080",
    "34.56.78.90:8080"
  ]
}
```

## n8n Integration

Use this URL in your n8n HTTP Request node:

```
https://api.apify.com/v2/acts/YOUR_USERNAME~cobb-county-jail-inquiry-scraper/run-sync-get-dataset-items?token=YOUR_APIFY_TOKEN
```

Pass the input as the POST body (JSON).
